sql:
SELECT project_id, COUNT(DISTINCT component_id) AS unique_components_used
FROM component_usage
GROUP BY project_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cp.component_id)
FROM component_properties cp
JOIN component_versions cv ON cp.component_id = cv.component_id;

SELECT DISTINCT component_id, usage_date
FROM component_usage
WHERE user_id IN (0, 1, 2);

external_knowledge:
- In this context, a "component" refers to a software component or module; 
- A "version" refers to a specific iteration or release of the component; 
- A "property" refers to a characteristic or attribute of the component; 
- "Usage" refers to the act of using or invoking the component within a project.

